        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 3:44PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Bluff City, or 10 miles east of Prescott, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bluff City.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
